    "header_color": "green",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "DIRECT OBJECT PRONOUNS replace the",
          "direct object (the 'what'/'whom').",
          "",
          "   me        mi    him/it (m)  lo",
          "   you       ti    her/it (f)  la",
          "                   you formal  La",
          "   us        ci    them (m)    li",
          "   you all   vi    them (f)    le",
          "",
          "POSITION: BEFORE the conjugated verb:",
          "   vedi Marco? — sì, lo vedo.",
          "   compri il libro? — sì, lo compro.",
          "   leggi le riviste? — sì, le leggo.",
          "",
          "ELISION before vowel/h:",
          "   l'ho visto = I saw him/it",
          "   l'amo = I love her/him"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lezione quattordici"
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "PAST PARTICIPLE AGREEMENT in passato",
          "prossimo with direct object pronouns:",
          "",
          "   ho visto Maria → l'ho vista",
          "   ho comprato i libri → li ho comprati",
          "   ho letto le riviste → le ho lette",
          "",
          "The participle agrees with the pronoun",
          "(lo/la/li/le) — NOT with mi/ti/ci/vi.",
          "",
          "WITH INFINITIVE — pronoun ATTACHES:",
          "   voglio vederlo (I want to see him)",
          "   devo leggerla (I have to read it)",
          "   vado a comprarli (I'm going to buy)",
          "",
          "NEGATIVE — 'non' goes before pronoun:",
          "   non lo vedo = I don't see him",
          "   non l'ho letto = I haven't read it"
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
